WEBVTT

00:11.505 --> 00:13.577
I'm a paramedic.
My name's Ilene.

00:13.677 --> 00:14.689
Are you in any pain?

00:16.350 --> 00:17.250
Scale of 1 to 10.

00:17.326 --> 00:18.526
It hurts to breathe.

00:18.920 --> 00:20.120
I'm okay, right?

00:20.320 --> 00:22.330
Try not to move.
You may have a rib fracture.

00:23.649 --> 00:25.349
I'll check on him now.

00:25.417 --> 00:26.951
Juan.

00:33.759 --> 00:36.093
Hey,
that's Juan Salazar, yo.

00:43.836 --> 00:46.237
You're going to help me
get her out of there. Come on.

00:51.944 --> 00:53.477
Can we wait till
help gets here?

00:53.545 --> 00:55.813
We are the help.
Everybody, back up.

00:55.881 --> 00:57.481
Aah! Oh!

00:57.549 --> 00:58.816
You're going
to pull her out.

00:58.884 --> 01:00.451
I need you to keep her
still and stable

01:00.519 --> 01:01.986
can you do that for me?

01:06.391 --> 01:08.693
It's ok. Ok.

01:08.744 --> 01:10.728
Steady. Breathe.

01:10.796 --> 01:12.780
Aah!

01:14.967 --> 01:17.168
Ok. I'm going to cut
the seat belt.

01:17.236 --> 01:18.569
When she falls,
catch her

01:18.604 --> 01:21.405
and guide her...

01:22.307 --> 01:25.309
Ok. Watch her spine.

01:25.377 --> 01:27.244
That's ok.

01:27.296 --> 01:29.547
Keep her spine supported.

01:31.049 --> 01:33.384
Gentle.
Support her.

01:35.587 --> 01:37.021
Go around her knees.

01:37.089 --> 01:38.472
On my count. Ready?

01:38.557 --> 01:40.224
1, 2, 3.

01:42.728 --> 01:44.428
Back up, now!

01:50.669 --> 01:53.103
SUV versus SUV
about a month ago.

01:53.155 --> 01:55.039
Cara Evans sustained
cracked ribs,

01:55.106 --> 01:56.941
a punctured lung,
and whiplash.

01:57.009 --> 01:59.443
Juan Salazar took
the brunt of the impact.

01:59.511 --> 02:00.678
Died instantly.

02:00.746 --> 02:02.747
Juan Salazar, he was
a baseball player.

02:02.814 --> 02:05.583
Best rookie pitcher
in the league.

02:05.651 --> 02:08.252
Donuts are going
like hotcakes.

02:08.320 --> 02:11.289
Oh?
I know that look.

02:11.356 --> 02:14.625
Assistant D.A. Jan Ottinger,
this is Dr. Cal Lightman.

02:14.693 --> 02:17.695
An assistant D.A. with no time
for small talk...

02:18.981 --> 02:21.265
Or donuts...

02:21.333 --> 02:24.035
Brings us
car crash footage.

02:25.687 --> 02:27.137
I smell a headline.

02:27.189 --> 02:30.041
3 guys were out joyriding
in that SUV.

02:30.108 --> 02:32.209
Fled the scene
unscathed.

02:32.277 --> 02:33.577
Vehicular
manslaughter?

02:33.645 --> 02:35.012
Try murder two.

02:35.080 --> 02:37.748
Really? Murder?

02:37.816 --> 02:39.317
Really.

02:43.789 --> 02:46.090
And while
the story's still hot,

02:46.158 --> 02:48.693
you want to know
which one was driving, huh.

02:48.760 --> 02:52.596
Well, we don't get kids
to rat out their mates

02:52.664 --> 02:54.015
just because you say so.

02:54.099 --> 02:55.933
It's a little more
complicated than that.

02:56.001 --> 02:59.537
Juan Salazar was a talented young man
cut down in his prime.

02:59.604 --> 03:02.073
Now, you wouldn't want
to stand in the way of justice,

03:02.140 --> 03:03.641
would you,
Dr. Lightman?

03:04.910 --> 03:08.346
Dr. Lightman?
What are you looking at?

03:08.413 --> 03:12.416
Hold the phone.
Stop the presses.

03:12.484 --> 03:15.386
Your headline's
about to change.

03:16.655 --> 03:19.390
That's guilt, that is.

03:20.692 --> 03:24.161
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Lie to Me 3x11 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Saved</font>
<font color=#FF7F00>Brand New Day</font> by Ryan Star

03:24.212 --> 03:28.132
♪ dream,
send me a sign ♪

03:28.200 --> 03:30.718
♪ turn back the clock ♪

03:30.802 --> 03:32.903
♪ give me some time ♪

03:32.971 --> 03:35.873
♪ I need to break out ♪

03:35.941 --> 03:38.075
♪ and make a new name ♪

03:38.143 --> 03:40.711
♪ let's open our eyes ♪

03:40.762 --> 03:47.718
♪ to the brand-new day ♪

