03:52.290 --> 03:53.491
Those 2 guys pacing
can't look at that one.

03:53.558 --> 03:54.959
That's guilt,
and they're also--

03:55.027 --> 03:56.610
Yeah, that is guilt.
They stole a car,

03:56.695 --> 03:58.129
and they killed
somebody.

03:58.196 --> 04:01.132
- Can I finish?
- Yes.

04:01.199 --> 04:04.335
That's guilt for what they did
to Juan Salazar.

04:04.403 --> 04:06.570
And shame for what they're about
to do to their buddy.

04:06.638 --> 04:09.140
Each is waiting for
the other to go first.

04:15.147 --> 04:17.447
You two, out.

04:17.516 --> 04:19.416
You're Mark, right?

04:19.468 --> 04:21.851
Sit down.
I want to talk to you.

04:26.925 --> 04:28.692
Want to give up
your friends?

04:28.760 --> 04:31.595
You're not a rat,
are you?

04:31.663 --> 04:33.531
Which is more than I can say
about them.

04:33.598 --> 04:36.901
They were going to give you up,
if I hadn't jumped in.

04:36.968 --> 04:38.903
You think
I'm full of it?

04:38.970 --> 04:41.405
I see that, too.
Flared nostrils,

04:41.473 --> 04:43.074
eyes narrowed--

04:43.141 --> 04:46.177
all of which is
totally understandable.

04:46.244 --> 04:49.797
But if I'm so full of it,

04:49.881 --> 04:53.317
how come I know,
from their faces,

04:53.385 --> 04:55.219
that you were the one
driving the SUV?

04:57.355 --> 04:59.840
- Oh, you must be his lawyer.
- Yeah.

04:59.925 --> 05:01.125
- Public defender?
- Yeah.

05:01.193 --> 05:03.094
It's ok.
He didn't say anything...

05:03.161 --> 05:04.128
Verbally.

05:04.196 --> 05:08.299
And I'm not a cop,
actually.

05:14.840 --> 05:16.941
What do we got?
Banger versus Glock.

05:17.008 --> 05:18.442
GSW to the chest.

05:18.510 --> 05:19.844
Pulse is 140
and thready.

05:19.911 --> 05:22.696
BP's 60 over 30, decreased breath
sounds on the left.

05:22.781 --> 05:24.648
- Has he been responsive at all?
- I don't know.

05:24.716 --> 05:27.284
Ok, on my count,
1, 2, 3.

05:27.352 --> 05:29.887
Lois,
get ready for intubation.

05:29.955 --> 05:32.206
Doug, we're going to need
a chest tube.

05:32.290 --> 05:34.175
I'll see you
in the garage.

05:40.165 --> 05:43.400
- You're amazing.
- Thank you.

05:43.468 --> 05:45.402
You know, I thought
I'd get that bit out of the way.

05:45.470 --> 05:47.805
You're amazing
at what you do.

05:47.873 --> 05:49.306
Dr. Cal Lightman.

05:49.374 --> 05:51.909
Ilene Clarke.
You new here, doctor?

05:51.977 --> 05:53.644
No, I'm not that kind of doctor,
darling.

05:53.712 --> 05:54.979
You going
up or down?

05:55.046 --> 05:57.214
Down. "B."
Thank you.

